parameters:
I haven't talked much with you before, and this is the
first time we're alone together.

I know that you're Kanade's friend, but I'm not sure
what to say...
Is it awkward being with me?
U-um, well... it's not really like that, but...

When I met Tsugumi, Kanae was always sticking close by
their side, so...
I've never been so troubled in a conversation before...
Um, what should I talk about...
Um, well, what do you like? Hobbies and stuff.
I think this is pretty normal.
No, no, I can't do anything like that.
Hikaru, weren't you living alone? And yet, you can't cook?

Well, I mostly eat out, like at convenience stores
and stuff.
You should quit that since it's not good for your health.
How about making food yourself and eating it now?

Kanae only eats meat, so I actually want them to eat out,
but Hikaru is the opposite.

Ah, that girl... she never ate any vegetables even when
eating bento.

It seems like everyone around here has a bad eating
habit.

I don't know if we'll become close, but... anyway, the
conversation itself is naturally continuing.

The awkward atmosphere that was there before seems to be
gradually improving.

You might think it's okay because you're young now, but
later when you get older...
No, this is the first time I've seen Tsugumi talk so much.
No, no, not in a bad way,
I don't usually hear it, but I think your voice is cute.
You're acting like an old man, Hikaru.
What? Because you call me old?

If someone called me auntie, I don't think I could bear
it.

Honestly, when talking about our eating habits, I did think a
little...
It's not good to say it out loud.

I will definitely make sure not to let it out from now
on.
I may have said a little too much.

When we talked about various things, Tsugumi was certainly
not a quiet girl.

Just a little clumsy and doesn't show emotions on their
face much.

Upon careful consideration, Saruyama often intentionally
provoked and was frequently verbally abused by her.

They might have a straightforward personality where they
say what they want to say.
